https://leetcode.com/problems/decode-string/description/

QUESTION:
Input: s = "3[a]2[bc]"
Output: "aaabcbc"

Input: s = "3[a2[c]]"
Output: "accaccacc"

SOLUTION:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(n) where n is total output size
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A number stack → to store repeat counts
A string stack → to store previous string states
curs → current working string
curn → current number being built
------------
MAIN IDEA:
------------
Number → build the repeat count
[ → save current number + string, reset both
Letters → add to current string
] → repeat current string and attach it to previous one
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public String decodeString(String s) {
        Stack<Integer>num=new Stack<>();
        Stack<String>st=new Stack<>();
        String curS="";
        int curN=0;
        char a[]=s.toCharArray();

        for(char ch:a){
            if(Character.isDigit(ch)){
                curN=curN*10+ch-'0';
            }else if(ch=='['){
                num.push(curN);
                st.push(curS);
                curS="";
                curN=0;
            }else if(ch==']'){
                StringBuilder sb=new StringBuilder();
                int time=num.pop();
                for(int i=0;i<time;i++){
                    sb.append(curS);
                }
                System.out.println(sb);
                curS=st.pop()+sb;
            }else{
                curS+=ch;
            }
        }
        return curS;
    }
}
